(r s = -0.34, p = 0.02). The present study indicates that high levels of MMP-2, 
perlecan, and TIMP-4 are associated with poor survival in PAH. High plasma 
MMP-2, correlated with poor prognosis in PAH. Further validation in larger 
studies is needed to better determine this association.

